    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-07T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-07T03:00:00-05:00" n="257"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.032/23: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-07T15:00:00+07:00"
                            >September 7, 1943—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1648. The C.E.C. plenary session opened September 6 with Chiang Kai-shek
                    presiding. In his opening address Chiang spoke of confidence in victory, but
                    requested that the session concentrate on the question of postwar
                    reconstruction.</p>
                <p>Informed Chinese now seem generally of opinion that question of a new President
                    will be resolved by Chiang’s continuing [in] the post of Acting President.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
